import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue', bins=30)
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flight delays?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Delay (minutes)")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(data=data, y='distance')
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    plt.axhline(avg_distance, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    origin_counts = data['origin'].value_counts().reset_index()
    destination_counts = data['destination'].value_counts().reset_index()

    origin_counts.columns = ['airport', 'count']
    destination_counts.columns = ['airport', 'count']

    combined_counts = pd.concat([origin_counts, destination_counts], axis=0)
    combined_counts = combined_counts.groupby('airport').sum().reset_index()

    chart = sns.barplot(x='airport', y='count', data=combined_counts)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title("What is the most common origin and destination for flights?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Airport")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Flights")
    plt.legend(["Flights"])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='distance', y='delay', hue='origin', palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between delay time and distance?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Delay')
    plt.legend(title='Origin', loc='upper right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.15, 1))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['date'] = data['date'].dt.to_period('M')
    flight_volume = data.groupby('date').size().reset_index(name='volume')

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='volume', data=flight_volume)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the trend in flight volume over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
